Storyline of 'Ghost'
Let me translate comments of @sunrise.6532 and others for you guys. Maybe this could help understanding more...

1. The real Jeff was probably a scientist or an astronaut in the military. He had a mission outside the world (from the first scene in GHOST, there was a spaceship)Real Jeff had invented an A.I. and the heroine witnesses this project too. Real Jeff worried about  his wife, so A.I Jeff came to take care of the wife and do farm work for her.
2. A.I. Jeff lives with the heroine, A.I. Jeff is gentle and caring. They felt in love and married with  a wooden ring.
3. The heroine loves A.I Jeff but when the real Jeff came back, the wife wore the platin wedding ring again. It means that the heroine has chosen the real Jeff.
4. The real Jeff, thw scientist kept experiment on A.I. Jeff but the heroine felt sorry for him and helped him escape to let him have his own life. And she wont find him, because she loves him.
5. In the end scene of 'Ghost', the heroine bid farewell to the A.I. Jeff and he even tried to convince her to run away with him but she denied even that was what she wanted. ( You could see from the last scene of Ghost that she ran after him and stop after A.I. rode the horse away.)

'Yellow Leaf' is represented A.l. Jeff's feeling.

The MV attempts to capture the idea that in some relationships, a person's connection or commitment can be elusive, like a game of hide-and-seek. No matter how hard they try to hide, the other person perceives that they only find an illusory or absent version of their partner, as if they are looking for a ghost. It indicates some frustration or disappointment in the search for a genuine connection.

The lyrics are a tapestry of poignant imagery, metaphorically comparing the love to a phantom, elusive and fading. It's a game of hide-and-seek where one partner, weary of searching, chooses to acknowledge the inevitable: goodbye.

I will explain the Mv in a nutshell. First you saw that there were two Jeffs, the "farmer" was a clone of the real Jeff (the "villain"), he was responsible for the clone, it was an experimental project and the woman was a clone.

If you notice the clone was betrayed by the person he loved the most, the MV you see how the woman takes off the ring the clone made for him to propose to her and then puts on the silver ring of her real husband when he was about to arrive, which meant that her work with the clone was about to end (this is seen in the part where the scientists arrive to grab the clone, he tries to fight but when he sees the real Jeff with his wife (this one with his ring and not the one he made her) being happy he sees his betrayal and then he gives up. 

Another thing, the clone had memories of a wedding (the real Jeff and the woman) that's why those scenes come out, they showed us what the clone had in mind, maybe he wanted to have his own memories and that's why he decided to ask the woman to marry him.

The woman really loved the clone (that's why almost at the end of the MV you see the woman going to the place where they had him, to free him), she fell in love with him, however she knew there was no point in staying with him because in the end he was just a "clone" of her real husband, the clone loved her too but he knew his place was not there and he had to let her go for her to be happy. 

At the end the woman stays with one of the two but I didn't quite understand that part because the Jeff they showed us has characteristics of the clone and the real Jeff, you can tell if you look closely at each one and at the end you compare them with the Jeff the woman stayed with.

By the way, Jeff will release his album in February tentatively, the main song will be "yellow leaf", this song is the continuation of this "ghost" story, maybe you will understand better the context and the story of this MV.

Smooth ring = military Jeff
Wire ring = clone/alien Jeff (aka soft Jeff)

Then in a series of flashbacks we see a happy wedding with smooth rings. This is Pretty Lady and Military jeff's wedding. Then we have flashes of blindfolded jeff going up to meet her in the bedroom. I believe this is also military jeff. Wedding night maybe? 

Switch to present - we see soft jeff making a wire ring, then proposing with the wire ring. She plays the blindfold game again but this time the Pretty Lady's surprise is calling back military jeff, we see her taking off the wire ring, putting back on the smooth ring and then we see military jeff's matching one. 

We see confrontation between military jeff and soft jeff, and that the pretty lady is taking notes in the background, because she's in on it.

So the timeline looks something like this:

military jeff and pretty lady are in love and get married
clone/alien jeff comes into their life, takes military jeff's form in some way  
military jeff leaves soft jeff with the pretty lady For Science, to see how much like military jeff this clone/alien/soft jeff is.
the answer is Very Similar Probably, because he also falls for jeff's Pretty Lady
Pretty Lady ends that part of the experiment and calls back her husband
Military jeff manhandles soft jeff and goes 'haha nerd, she's mine'
soft jeff makes extremely sad eyes
Pretty Lady decides she has a heart, and probably even loved soft jeff too, helps him escape. 
soft jeff rides off into the sunset
